Author-Name:  E. Glen Weyl 
Author-Name:  Jean Tirole 
Title: Market Power Screens Willingness-to-Pay 
Abstract:
 What is the best way to reward innovation? While prizes avoid deadweight
 loss, intellectual property (IP) selects high social surplus projects.
 Optimal innovation policy thus trades off the ex ante screening benefit
 and the ex post distortion. It solves a multidimensional screening problem
 in the private information held by the innovator: research cost, quality,
 and market size of the innovation. The appropriate degree of market power
 is never full monopoly pricing and is determined by measurable market
 characteristics, the inequality and elasticity of innovation supply,
 making the analysis open to empirical calibration. The framework has
 applications beyond IP policy to the optimal pricing of platforms or the
 optimal procurement of public infrastructure.  Copyright 2012, Oxford University Press.
